      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Competitive. QUICK COOKIE (3) placed at Bunbury and then Belmont before leading at Belmont over a bit shorter, where she folded up late. Won't know herself in country grade and will be tough to beat. MYZOOM (6) held on to place at Belmont over a mile, quickly back on track. Is on a quick back-up and she will enjoy a soft run from an inside barrier. Should be right in it. SHEEZA SHEILA (7) was well held last time at Ascot over 1800m but is going well enough generally to be considered at this level. Peaks and the blinkers go on for the first time. POLYVANOVA (1) has switched yards since finishing third three weeks ago over 1850m at Mt Barker. Kept up to the mark with a recent placing in a Lark Hill trial and is well placed with the 3kg claim. She's also a chance.",
